<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 2:13PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Seminole,
north central Pontotoc, south central Pottawatomie and west central
Hughes Counties through 245 PM CDT...
At 212 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Konawa, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail. Large amounts of small hail that may result
in hazardous travel and localized flooding.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wewoka, Konawa, Sasakwa and Spaulding.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
